wasp cli

- wasp start: start client and server

- wasp db migrate-dev: update db after changing schema.prisma models/entities

- wasp db studio: open browser db client

If you make a change to models/entities, operations (queries and actions) or tsx that uses them, currently, since we're using typescript, it may not automatically rebuild correctly. You can fix with:

- Stop and restart with `wasp start`
- In a ts/js/tsx file, cmd-p > Typescript: Restart TS server

Typescript adds enough value that it's worth this to me until wasp fixes it.
